  "claim_boundary": "proven_for_finite_bound",
  "analysis": "Exhaustive stopping-time computation for all n in [1, 10,000,000] confirms every checked trajectory reaches 1. Maximum stopping time observed: 685 steps. The finite-sample cumulative stopping-time fraction is nondecreasing by construction and has d_200 = 0.774346; this does not verify Terras's theorem. The Kolmogorov\u2013Smirnov comparison against sigma(n) ~ log2(n)/log2(4/3) yields D = 0.980020; this large discrepancy rejects close distributional agreement on the tested normalization. Residue-class and record tables are descriptive and establish no asymptotic growth law. This is a finite-bound exhaustive certificate; the full conjecture remains open."
